Don't forget to mark your calendars for Friday, May 19 for our SMART Start to Summer EVENT!

WHEN: 1:00-3:00 on Friday, May 19

FREE Bike Helmets to the first 50 K-12 students in attendance.

FREE Balloon Animals

Each classroom will need supplies to decorate with. If you would like to assist by sending in supplies (ex: stickers, pom poms, glitter glue, feathers, etc.) for your child's classroom please send them with your child to give to their teacher by Wednesday morning.

The next event we will begin preparing for will be Fall Class parties. We will send more information out on this soon. The craft we are currently planning on will use empty 2 liter bottles. If you can assist by collecting empty bottles, rinsing, removing the labels (and adhesive) we would greatly appreciate your help! post_text:
Thank you to everyone who supported and participated in our first annual PTA sponsored Read-A-Thon! We had very high expectations for our first fundraiser event and are pleased with the amount of money raised based on the number of kids we had participate.
We had 39 of 348 Elementary students participate, which unfortunately was only 11% of our students but we are quite pleased to announce that we raised $2,300 from these dedicated participants, which was 46% of our $5,000 goal!
We also want to thank again our local businesses and other supporters who helped make this event possible!
Hillbilly Gas Mart
Smart Insurance Agency
S&A Plumbing Company
Woody's Express Trucking
HMD Accounting & Tax
Marionville Athletic Boosters
Wayne & Linda Woody
Alpine Wood Products
Bank of Billings
The Compound
Young Kearns Construction
Heather Woody
Thank you again!!

Read-A-Thon Extension! We have extended the Read-A-Thon through the weekend (now ending Sunday night, 11/3/13) to give the kids a little extra time to accomplish their goals. We received some great feedback that after seeing the prizes at school the kids have really been motivated. All flat rate donations will be due Monday, November 4th. The per minute pledges will be due no later than Monday, November 11th. If the money is not turned in by the 11th they will not be entered into the iPod drawing for the top money producer. Prizes will be announced Friday, November 15th.

Dates to remember:

November 4th ‚Äì All forms must be turned in and flat rate money collected
November 11th - Per minute pledges must be turned in
November 13th ‚Äì Prizes will be announced

post_text: We are still looking for 10 volunteers for our first AWESOME Family Fun Night Dec 1, 4-6!! We are going to have a chili cook off, crafts, face painting, AND pictures with Santa!! We are also going to have amazing raffle prizes!! You don't want to miss it!!
